06.","meanings":["English (southern):","of Norman origin, from Anglo-Norman French and Middle English <i>Haueis</i>, <i>Hawis</i>, from an Old French form of the ancient Germanic female personal name <i>Hadewidis</i> (from <i>had-</i> ‘war’ + <i>wid-</i> with a range of possible original meanings).","variant of   Haw  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Haw","meanings":["English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Haw(e)</i> which, like <i>Daw(e)</i>, was probably a rhyming pet form of Middle English <i>Raw</i> (Ralph). Similar rhyming pet forms of other Anglo-Norman male personal names beginning with <i>R-</i> are found in <i>Hick</i> and <i>Dick</i> for <i>Rick</i> (Richard) and <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i> for <i>Rob(ert)</i>. See also   Hawkin  .","English: topographic name for someone who lived by an enclosure, from Middle English <i>hawe</i> ‘enclosure’ (Old English <i>haga</i> or Old Norse <i>hagi</i>). Compare   Haugh  .","Chinese: variant Romanization of the surnames 何 and 賀, see   He   1 and 2."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice Hawes was born in 1453, in Norwich, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with Thomas Calthrop. She died in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1453–":"1453–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1474–Female":"1474–Surnud","1453–Female":"1453–Surnud","1453":"1453","1474":"1474","abt 1474":"umbes 1474","Norwich, Norfolk, England":"Norwich, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of Pockthorp, Norwich, England":"Norwich, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1453–":"1453–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1474–Female":"1474–Kuollut","1453–Female":"1453–Kuollut","1453":"1453","1474":"1474","abt 1474":"noin 1474","Norwich, Norfolk, England":"Norwich, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","of Pockthorp, Norwich, England":"Norwich, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1453–":"1453–Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","1474–Female":"1474–Décédée","1453–Female":"1453–Décédée","1453":"1453","1474":"1474","abt 1474":"environ 1474","Norwich, Norfolk, England":"Norwich, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","of Pockthorp, Norwich, England":"Norwich, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Alice Hawes est née en 1453, à Norwich, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec Thomas Calthrop. Elle est décédée à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni."},"de":{"1453–":"1453–Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","1474–Female":"1474–Verstorben","1453–Female":"1453–Verstorben","1453":"1453","1474":"1474","abt 1474":"um 1474","Norwich, Norfolk, England":"Norwich, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","England":"England, United Kingdom","of Pockthorp, Norwich, England":"Norwich, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Alice Hawes wurde 1453 in Norwich, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom geboren. Sie hatte mit Thomas Calthrop mindestens 1 Tochter. Sie starb in England, United Kingdom."},"ht":{"1453–":"1453–Desede","–Male":"Desede","1474–Female":"1474–Desede","1453–Female":"1453–Desede","1453":"1453",